(414, 'NcNAzhB1qqUNv4brH8tSuA==', 1, '\n\nContent marketing is one of the most common ways to generate more traffic to your website. If you want to increase the number of visitors on your site, then content is the way to do it. When you publish great content that’s valuable and helpful for readers, they will be attracted by it and visit your site more often. This article will show you how content marketing can increase traffic on any website or blog in the long run.\n\nWhat You Need To Know About Content Marketing:\n\nThe first thing that you need to know about content marketing is that it’s not a new concept at all – this has been around for years now, but only recently have we begun seeing a widespread adoption of this strategy among businesses and marketers alike. Whether you are already using this strategy or are just getting started with it, here are some tips for making sure that your efforts pay off:\n\n1) Make sure there’s value in what you write…and make sure there’s value in what others write as well! You don’t want people to come back because they think they should (or because someone paid them), but because they like what they see when visiting your site or checking out an article on another site (or even how much time they spend reading). Don’t just throw up articles', 1, '2022-10-29', '14:36:14', '2022-11-16 15:41:12'),
(415, 'x3mHp3aDzidIDR5E5fFlRw==', 161, 'Working from home is great because  you can do it at the same time as your family and still get plenty of work done. However, you have to be careful that you don’t fall into a trap of doing all the housework yourself, because then you won’t see any progress. You need to set aside your own time for work so that you can be successful at home alone.\n\nIf your goal is to make money online, affiliate marketing is a great option. An affiliate is someone who promotes products on their website. If people click through and buy a product or service over an affiliate link on that website, the person making money is the one who gets paid while the person who originally sent them to the product or service gets commensurate credit for their recommendation (paraphrased). There are many ways this works:\n\nIf there\'s a specific product or service you need and it\'s not listed, fill out this form and we\'ll put it on our list of available services: https://goo.gl/forms/9aJ0gvwC2vQk1yD2. We will also contact you if there are any updates to our site that may affect your ability to receive these services in future months!\nThere are loads of resources for making money online as an affiliate. You could source products from ClickBank,', 1, '2022-11-01', '22:52:43', '2022-11-16 15:41:12'),
(416, 'Dcdz8cPa9tsDZB2v2MUzKg==', 161, 'Written by Jasper. Cc@kenken &amp;the unschooled man<br>Blog Title: The Battle of the Content: Jasper AI vs Human Writers<br>Blog Introduction: In the red corner, we have Jasper AI, the newest kid on the block when it comes to content creation. And in the blue corner, we have Human Writers, tried and true champions of the content world. Who will win this showdown? Let\'s find out!<br>Blog Body:<br>The Case for Jasper AI<br>There\'s no denying that Jasper AI is fast. Arguably, it\'s too fast. Once you hit that \"Publish\" button, there\'s no going back. But speed isn\'t everything, right? Well, in Jasper AI\'s case, it kind of is. See, with Jasper AI, you don\'t have to worry about things like writer\'s block or taking too long to churn out a piece of content. That\'s because Jasper AI can do it all for you in a fraction of the time! All you need is a topic and a target word count, and Jasper AI will take care of the rest. Plus, since Jasper AI is powered by A.I., you can be sure that your content will be free of any grammar or spelling errors.<br>The Case for Human Writers<br>Human writers may not be as fast as Jasper AI, but they more than make up for it in quality. After all, there\'s nothing quite like the human touch when it comes to creating content that resonates with readers. With human writers, you also get the added bonus of being able to provide feedback and make changes before anything goes live. That way, you can be sure that your finished product is exactly what you want it to be.<br>Conclusion:<br>So which is better? Jasper AI or Human Writers? The answer is…it depends! If you\'re looking for speed and quantity over quality, then Jasper AI is the way to go. But if you want your content to pack a real punch and connect with your audience on a deeper level, then human writers are your best bet. Whichever route you choose, just remember that at the end of the day, good content is still good content—regardless of who (or what) writes it!', 1, '2022-11-02', '19:47:37', '2022-11-16 15:41:12');
