(420, 'Rsf/ITQvJEJdr55QVjLI1g==', 161, 'Textcortex Sample:The Battle of the Content: Jasper AI vs Human Writers<br><br>In this article, I will be talking about a battle between two people — A human writer and an artificial intelligence.<br><br>About Jasper AI<br><br>Jasper is an algorithm that helps writers make better content faster.<br>Jasper is a tool that gives writers more time to write. It’s designed to help writers write more easily. It’s not a replacement for a human, but rather a complement.<br><br>Why use an AI Writer?<br><br>There are many reasons why you should be using an artificial intelligence (AI) to write.<br><br>1. You don’t have to worry about grammar or spelling mistakes<br><br>With an AI writer, your work goes directly to the machine. No need to manually edit, proofread, or edit for grammar or spelling mistakes.<br><br><div>2. Your writing will be error-free</div><div><br></div>3. Your writing will be free of plagiarism<br><br>4. Your writing will be delivered on time<br><br>5. You will be able to communicate with your writer<br><br>6. You will be able to order revisions if you are not satisfied with your paper<br><br>7. You will be able to get a refund if your paper is delivered late or if it does not meet your expectations<br><br>8. You will be able to get a refund if your paper is delivered late or if it', 1, '2022-11-02', '20:16:29', '2022-11-16 15:41:12'),
(422, 'd67oKOYiwNgWGiiP8ZQzOQ==', 161, 'Jasper AI Sample: The Battle of the Content: Jasper AI vs Human Writers<br><br>Blog Introduction: In the red corner, we have Jasper AI, the newest kid on the block when it comes to content creation. And in the blue corner, we have Human Writers, tried and true champions of the content world. Who will win this showdown? Let\'s find out!<br><br>Blog Body<br>The Case for Jasper AI<br>There\'s no denying that Jasper AI is fast. Arguably, it\'s too fast. Once you hit that \"Publish\" button, there\'s no going back. But speed isn\'t everything, right? Well, in Jasper AI\'s case, it kind of is. See, with Jasper AI, you don\'t have to worry about things like writer\'s block or taking too long to churn out a piece of content. That\'s because Jasper AI can do it all for you in a fraction of the time! All you need is a topic and a target word count, and Jasper AI will take care of the rest. Plus, since Jasper AI is powered by A.I., you can be sure that your content will be free of any grammar or spelling errors.<br><br>The Case for Human Writers<br>Human writers may not be as fast as Jasper AI, but they more than make up for it in quality. After all, there\'s nothing quite like the human touch when it comes to creating content that resonates with readers. With human writers, you also get the added bonus of being able to provide feedback and make changes before anything goes live. That way, you can be sure that your finished product is exactly what you want it to be.<br><br>Conclusion<br>So which is better? Jasper AI or Human Writers? The answer is…it depends! If you\'re looking for speed and quantity over quality, then Jasper AI is the way to go. But if you want your content to pack a real punch and connect with your audience on a deeper level, then human writers are your best bet. Whichever route you choose, just remember that at the end of the day, good content is still good content—regardless of who (or what) writes it!<br>', 1, '2022-11-02', '20:20:10', '2022-11-16 15:41:12'),
(425, '1Ve/+qkDs5VgTTzoRpoAJg==', 161, 'Kurt Reimer Every micro niche has thousands of highly interested people. Every topic has micro niches. There are new topics and niches being created every day. Most are still underserved. Some niches won’t last forever but if they’re reasonably evergreen and you go really deep they last and you can make excellent returns from fewer visitors.<br>What isn’t working anymore (without huge investment) is skimming the top of a topic broadly. That’s a big publishing company game.<br>If your budget is like this then do this, basically:<br>$0 to $5k -&gt; build your own deep micro niche site on a topic you’re passionate about that has an obvious following and some expensive products (new topics are great because competition is nil, but you need first hand knowledge)<br>ex: archery -&gt; bow fishing -&gt; bow fishing for carp<br>ex: bikes -&gt; ebikes -&gt; ebike batteries<br>$10-20k<br>ex: archery -&gt; bow fishing<br>$100k+<br>ex: archery<br>When in doubt, go deeper.<br>In the $10-100k budget range it’s often better to buy and merge existing sites than try to build from the ground up. Building authority in a broader topic without consistent YouTube and social presence is tough. Building 10k+ backlinks doesn’t happen overnight.<br>You need a substantial budget for writers, editors and backlinks, and probably email and social marketing. Many sites flatten out around the 10-30k for lack of these elements.<br>I think the average person should side hustle 2-3 good micro niche sites to learn. If one takes off then go all-in. This is way less risky than declaring you’re a full time blogger with no income.<br>Also, websites are still substantially less risky and have better returns than other business models. The business model is WAY simpler. Most of the time there are no employees except the owner. Outsourcing content and marketing means no HR accounting, insurance, taxes, hiring/firing, etc. Lawsuits are extremely rare. Your customers can be anywhere in the world which mitigates geographic risk. The amount of money and payback period on content investment is usually 2 years or less, much shorter than traditional business loans. <br>', 1, '2022-11-03', '14:48:36', '2022-11-16 15:41:12'),
(428, 'UWe5YMnjbVUtZ4Ikdoo0vg==', 161, 'Blog Title: Jasper AI Content: The Pros, the Cons, and the In-Betweens<br>Blog Introduction: Content is king, they say. Or is it? In recent years, there has been a surge in the use of AI-generated content. But is this just a passing fad? Is AI-generated content really worth your time and effort? Let\'s take a closer look at the pros and cons of Jasper AI content to see if it\'s really worth your while.<br>Blog Body:<br>The Pros of Jasper AI Content<br>1. It\'s fast. Really fast.<br>If you need content yesterday, Jasper AI is your best bet. With the push of a button, you can have an entire blog post or whitepaper written in minutes. All you need to do is enter in a few parameters, such as word count, target audience, etc., and Jasper AI will generate high-quality content that is sure to please.<br>2. It\'s cost-effective.<br>Needless to say, time is money. And if you\'re able to generate quality content in a fraction of the time (and cost) it would take to produce manually, then that\'s definitely a win in our book.<br>3.It\'s scalable.<br>Another big pro of Jasper AI is its scalability. With traditional methods of content generation, it can be quite difficult (and costly) to scale up your output quickly and efficiently. However, with Jasper AI, you can simply add more licenses as needed and instantly increase your output tenfold without breaking the bank.<br>The Cons of Jasper AI Content<br>1.It lacks emotionality .<br>One downside of Jasper AI content is that it can often lack emotionality or personality. This isn\'t necessarily a bad thing—after all, not every piece of content needs to be dripping with personality—but it\'s something to keep in mind when deciding whether or not Jasper AI is right for your needs.<br>2.It can be difficult to make edits .<br>Another downside of Jasper AI-generated content is that it can be difficult (though not impossible) to make edits after the fact. This is due to the fact that much of the \"content\" is actually generated by algorithms rather than human beings. As such, there can be a bit of a learning curve when it comes to making changes or additions after the fact.<br>3..It\'s not perfect .<br>Of course, no technology is perfect—and Jasper AI content is no exception. Despite its many advantages, there are still some areas where Jasper AI falls short (though we imagine that will change as the technology continues to evolve). For example, at present there are some issues with grammar and syntax when using Jasper AI to generate longer pieces of content such as blog posts or articles. However, we expect these issues will be ironed out in future iterations of the software . Conclusion: So there you have it: the pros and cons of Jasper AI content generation! Is it right for you? Only you can answer that question—but we hope this overview has helped you reach a decision!', 1, '2022-11-04', '09:22:14', '2022-11-16 15:41:12'),
(429, 'ZKuXSoQKfgw3IAgsZQ+VwQ==', 161, 'Blog Title: Content: The Age-Old Showdown<br>Blog Introduction: It seems like everywhere you look, there\'s a new form of content marketing taking over the internet. Whether it\'s \"native advertising,\" \"content curation,\" or that one guy who always seems to be selling something on his blog, it\'s hard to escape the never-ending onslaught of new ideas and strategies. In the midst of all this change, one thing remains the same: the age-old debate of human-written vs machine-generated content. So, which is better? Let\'s take a closer look.<br>Blog Body:<br>On the one hand, you have human-written content. This is the traditional form of content marketing, in which a real live human being sits down at a computer andbang out a blog post, article, or social media update. On the other hand, you have machine-generated content, which is created using artificial intelligence (AI) algorithms. So, which is better?<br>There are pros and cons to both human-written and machine-generated content. Human-written content has the advantage of being able to convey complex emotions and ideas, while machine-generated content can be produced at a much faster pace and with less effort. However, machine-generated content often suffers from poor grammar and can lack the personal touch that makes human-written content so effective.<br>At the end of the day, there is no clear winner in the human-written vs machine-generated content debate. It really depends on your specific needs and goals as a business. If you need to produce a lot of content quickly and efficiently, then machine-generated content might be the way to go. But if you\'re looking to build a strong emotional connection with your audience, then human-written content is probably a better bet.<br>Conclusion:<br>The showdown between human-written and machine-generated content has been going on for years, with no clear winner in sight. It really depends on your specific needs as a business as to which type of content will work best for you. If you need to produce a lot of content quickly and efficiently, then machine-generated content might be the way to go. But if you\'re looking to build a strong emotional connection with your audience, then human-writtencontent is probably a better bet.', 1, '2022-11-04', '09:22:49', '2022-11-16 15:41:12'),
(435, 'pmq8FjMQ09i/p78xMkamGA==', 161, 'Quora is a hidden gem for many SEO specialists (that can bring you tons of organic traffic without investing a lot!)<br><br>Imagine a situation: Your business is in a highly competitive niche. You want to rank for the keyword X, but all of the results on page one are DR 70+ and have tons of backlinks.<br>Should you miss this opportunity?<br>Definitely no. Especially if a Quora question ranks on the 1st page for your search term.<br>Here is what you can do:<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Go to Ahrefs and scrape the list of the results for your competitive terms that contain Quora answers on the 1st page.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Write in-depth answers with a quick mention of how your business solves this problem.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; If the Quora question is full of answers, promote your answer with Quora\'s Promoted Answers (it\'s insanely cheap!)<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Boom! You\'re ranking on the 1st page on Google, among business leaders who spent thousands of $$$ on SEO, without a zero link built.<br><br>This strategy could be a great temporary solution while you are growing your page related to the same search term organically.<br>Alternatively, you can use this strategy to get multiple spots on page one.', 1, '2022-11-04', '16:14:18', '2022-11-16 15:41:12'),
(436, 'fEPSTf5wttbHxw7gW8n1eA==', 161, 'ShortlyAI<br>Get past the dreaded blinking cursor.&lt;/div&gt;Just click the button and your AI partner will continue writing for you, in your own voice.<br><br>Try it free now<br>Turn your thoughts into fully-fleshed prose.<br>Whether you are writing your next best-selling novel, or a blog post for your website, our state-of-the-art AI will help you turn your thoughts into well-written paragraphs.<br><br>Turn to it when you need a creative brainstorming partner, or when you want to expand and develop a thought.<br><br>All in a clean, blank, distraction-free interface.', 1, '2022-11-04', '16:15:59', '2022-11-16 15:41:12'),
(437, '0f2Jc9A1kpPaBv620UEqNQ==', 161, '<div>It seems like everywhere you look, there\'s a new form of content marketing taking over the internet. Whether it\'s \"native advertising,\" \"content curation,\" or that one guy who always seems to be selling something on his blog, it\'s hard to escape the never-ending onslaught of new ideas and strategies. In the midst of all this change, one thing remains the same: the age-old debate of human-written vs machine-generated content. So, which is better? Let\'s take a closer look.</div><div><br></div><div>Human-Written Content\n\nPros:\n\n1. It\'s personal.\n\nWhen you write something yourself, it\'s bound to be more personal than something that was written by a machine. This is because humans are able to express themselves in a way that machines simply cannot. We\'re able to use our emotions and experiences to connect with our audience on a deeper level, which is something that machines are not yet able to do.\n\n2. It\'s more trustworthy.\n\nSince human-written content is more personal, it\'s also more trustworthy. When you read something that was written by a real person, you know that they\'re sharing their honest opinion and not just trying to sell you something. This is not the case with machine-generated content, which is often full of marketing jargon and empty promises.\n\n3. It\'s more engaging.\n\nHuman-written content is also more engaging than machine-generated content. This is because humans are able to tell stories and use humor in a way that machines cannot. We\'re also able to use our unique experiences to connect with our audience on a more personal level, which is something that machines are not yet able to do.\n\nCons:\n\n1. It\'s more expensive.\n\nSince human-written content is more personal and engaging, it\'s also more expensive. This is because it takes more time and effort to write something that is both well-written and interesting to read. <br></div><div><br></div><div>2. It\'s less consistent.\n\nSince human-written content is more personal, it\'s also less consistent. This is because humans are not able to write in the same voice all the time. We\'re also not able to write at the same level of quality all the time, which can make it difficult for your audience to connect with your brand.\n\n3. It\'s more likely to be plagiarized.\n\nSince human-written content is more personal, it\'s also more likely to be plagiarized. This is because it\'s easy for someone to copy your work and claim it as their own.<br></div><br>', 1, '2022-11-08', '15:23:10', '2022-11-16 15:41:12'),
(438, 'gi59Vl6BIHYRcUQ5dBQS8A==', 161, '<div>It seems like everywhere you look, there\'s a new form of content marketing taking over the internet. Whether it\'s \"native advertising,\" \"content curation,\" or that one guy who always seems to be selling something on his blog, it\'s hard to escape the never-ending onslaught of new ideas and strategies. In the midst of all this change, one thing remains the same: the age-old debate of human-written vs machine-generated content. So, which is better? Let\'s take a closer look.Human-Written Content\n\nHuman-written content is, well, written by humans. This can include everything from blog posts and articles to eBooks and whitepapers. The main advantage of human-written content is that it can be customized to meet the specific needs of your audience. For example, if you\'re targeting a specific niche or market, you can create content that\'s specifically tailored to their interests.\n\nAnother advantage of human-written content is that it\'s generally more engaging than machine-generated content. This is because humans are able to infuse their personality into their writing, which makes it more relatable and interesting to read. Finally, human-written content is more likely to be shared on social media and other online platforms, which can help to increase your reach and visibility.\n\nMachine-Generated Content\n\nMachine-generated content is, as the name suggests, created by machines. This can include anything from automated blog posts to eBooks that are generated by algorithms. The main advantage of machine-generated content is that it can be created quickly and easily. For example, if you need to create a large amount of content in a short period of time, machine-generated content is a great option.\n\nAnother advantage of machine-generated content is that it can be highly targeted. This is because algorithms can be used to target specific keywords and phrases, which can help to improve your search engine optimization (SEO). Finally, machine-generated</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><br>', 1, '2022-11-08', '15:24:51', '2022-11-16 15:41:12'),
(439, 'GDvbHIQiDeHkOQlGnWAnOA==', 1, 'He had just started watching a movie when there was a knock at the door.\n\nHe paused the movie and got up to answer it.\n\nWhen he opened the door, he saw his neighbor standing there with a package in her hand.\n\n\"Hi, neighbor,\" she said. \"I was just about to go to the post office and I saw that you had a package sitting on your porch. I didn\'t want it to get stolen, so I brought it inside for you.\"\n\n\"Oh, thank you,\" he said, taking the package from her.\n\n\"You\'re welcome,\" she said. \"Have a nice day.\"\n\n\"You too,\" he said, before closing the door.\n\nHe looked at the package and saw that it was from his online streaming service.\n\nHe opened it up and found that it was a free trial of their new premium service.\n\nHe was about to cancel it, but then he thought about how much he loved movies and decided to give it a try.', 1, '2022-11-09', '10:56:48', '2022-11-16 15:41:12'),
