(446, 'sjFoXzCFO2ZAyBpt0FTwTQ==', 161, 'Working from home is great because  you can do it in your pajamas. You don’t have to get dressed, and you can go about your day without making a big deal out of it. But, there are some things that need to be considered before going into the world of remote work.\n\nThere are many different types of remote jobs out there for people with all different skill sets and experience levels. This guide will help you find the right type of job that fits your needs, so you can make the most money possible while working from home!\n\nWhy Should I Be Working From Home?\n<br><div>Working from home has become very popular over the last few years due to many reasons including: cost savings, flexibility, less stress and more time for yourself. If you’re considering a career change or want to increase your income then working at home may be a good option for you! There are many benefits available when working remotely including: more money, less stress and more time for yourself! Here are some key points on why people choose this type of job: More Money – Working at home means having access to flexible hours which allow us to fit our work around our personal life (more on this later). Less Stress – Many companies offer benefits such as paid leave or childcare which allows employees who work remotely full-time access to these services without</div>', 1, '2022-11-12', '09:13:24', '2022-11-16 15:41:12'),
(450, 'Hn7CdHFlWSlFznGO+40Veg==', 1, 'If you have a knack for organization, you can make money online as a virtual assistant helping people to keep their days in order. A virtual assistant will do everything from bookkeeping to research, database entry, booking travel, and managing email. It can also be an awesome way to rub shoulders with some very important people, build up your professional network, and of course grow another stream of income. You can find great gigs on UpWork, Fiverr, Indeed, and Remote.co.\n\nIf you’re looking for work as a graphic designer or web developer, you don’t need to spend $50-$100 an hour just to get started. Specialize in one thing — such as logo design or web design — and do it well. Then once you have a portfolio of your own work, you can start charging more money and learning about new areas within your industry.\n\n4. Create a website for yourself\n\nA website is an excellent way to showcase your work and get it in front of potential clients. You can use it as a portfolio, or even sell your own products on there (assuming you have the time to create them). It’s also a great place\n\nThink of it like this: If you’re a freelancer, you’re the only one who owns your work. You are the only person who has access to it and can decide whether or not to share it with others. This is a huge advantage for freelancers as they are able to<br>', 1, '2022-11-16', '17:55:55', '2022-11-16 15:41:12'),
