(493, 'H7IgTIJWX1nRGzFQBUzUIg==', 1, 'The following is a conversation between a web developer named Kelvin and his client, Francesca. Kelvin was to be paid for helping develop websites and write content for them, among other tasks. Kelvin wants help in crafting a message highlighting his plight and why he should receive payment soon after such a long wait.<br><br>Kelvin\'s first message: \"Hey Francesca, I trust you\'re well. I\'m just checking with you to see where we stand in terms of work, payment and the way forward. I know you\'ve been and are quite busy but I was hoping you could spare a moment to share your thoughts on the aforementioned.\"<br><br>Kelvin\'s second message: \"Hey Francesca, <br><br>I haven\'t heard from you for some time now. I last reached out more than 2 weeks ago, are things okay? I needed to know where we stand regarding work and payment so I can make plans for my living. <br><br>Please do let me know when I can expect to receive the outstanding payment. It has been more than 3 months since the last one and I unfortunately haven\'t had the chance to brace for my current situation.<br><br>I really hope to hear from you before making any decision. Thanks.\"<br><br>Francesca\'s reply after some time: \"I know Kelvin, I am so so sorry for the delay and delay in reply. I was away and I thought everything would be ready to sort out once I got back but it is not yet. Apologies Kelvin, I am still chasing payments from my brother and since the currency has crashed here this is taking a long time. Since I have not been paid any back payments I have nothing to pass forward until that happens. I will let you know as soon as I do and then I will review the timesheets. I know it is frustrating, I am frustrated myself and having to borrow money myself to cover expenses until I get any of the payments.\"<br><br>Kelvin\'s reply: \"It\'s OK, I understand now - I needed to know what was happening on your end so I can plan my next move. As it stands, I too have been forced to borrow and make compromises as I wasn\'t prepared for the delay. It\'s unfortunate but we have to wait it out, I guess. Anyways, I hope things turn for the better soon before it gets any worse.\"<br><br>It is now 2 months since Kelvin sent the above reply. He is still yet to receive any payment. What should he say next so that the client makes the payment as soon as possible?<br><br>Kelvin: \"Hey Francesca! I hope you\'re doing well. I\'m writing to check in and see if there has been any progress on the payment front. It\'s now been two months since I last heard from you and I\'m still yet to receive any payment. I\'m sure you understand how difficult this situation has been for me, as I\'m sure it has been for you. I\'m hoping that you can help me out here and make the payment as soon as possible. I would really appreciate it if you could do this for me. Thank you for your understanding and I look forward to hearing from you soon.\" <br>', 1, '2022-11-29', '14:11:10', '2022-11-29 11:11:10');
