(533, '7iewUNdyKV133HdDhE8h+g==', 1, 'I\'m a freelance web developer. &nbsp;I started working for someone (Francesca) in the UK a few months ago but they have been taking a long time to settle the outstanding payment. It\'s been almost six months since the payment was due as of today, and I\'m really struggling to make ends meet. I\'ve tried reaching out to her a few times, but she always has an excuse for why the payment is delayed.<br><br>The first excuse was that she was waiting on payments from her own clients and needed to invoice her brother (she sort of sub-contracted me for a web project by her brother). Then, she told me that the currency had crashed in her country (she blamed Brexit) and she was having trouble getting the payment to me. I was really understanding and patient at first, but as the months went by and the payment still didn\'t come through, I started to get really worried. I\'ve had to borrow money just to afford basic necessities like food, and I\'m really struggling to make ends meet.<br><br>What\'s been really frustrating is the fact that she seems to ignore my requests. I haven\'t been messaging her incessantly - far from that. Her last reply was two months ago and I had to wait almost a month for it. I have only messaged her once since then and that was a month ago. We used to communicate daily on WhatsApp and she\'d reply within seconds back then.<br><br>I should say that something she did on the very last day I worked for her spooked me. She seemed to be parting ways with me albeit very indirectly. I mean, she asked me to transfer and change ownership of all docs, passwords e.t.c. (and rightfully so) to her. She also mentioned that she\'d be sending some payment through \"soon\" (of course that didn\'t happen). She never mentioned that she was cancelling the project I was working on but that was the last day she sent work my way. It seemed to me that she\'d made up her mind earlier but wasn\'t willing to explicitly tell me so for God kn