ltiple HDMI ports and USB ports  \n\nâ— Audio Quality: Both TVs have good audio quality with built-in speakers  \n\nâ— Price Range: The Samsung S95B starts at $2,199.99 while the Sony A90J starts at $2,799.99  \n\n  \n\nSamsung S95C vs Sony A90J: Whatâ€™s the Difference? \n\nDisplay Technology - The biggest difference between these two TVs is the display technology they use. The Samsung S95C utilizes Quantum Dot (QD) OLED technology while the Sony A90J uses traditional OLED technology. QD-OLED offers brighter colors and higher contrast ratios than traditional OLEDs and can be viewed from wider angles without losing image quality.  \n\nBrightness - The Samsung S95C gets a bit brighter than the Sony A90J in general use due to its QD-OLED display technology. It also has brighter colors thanks to its improved color accuracy compared to traditional OLEDs.  \n\nPrice Range - The price range for these two TVs varies depending on screen size but generally speaking, the Samsung S95B is slightly cheaper than the Sony A90J for comparable sizes.  \n\nGaming Compatibility - The Samsung TV has wider gaming compatibility as it supports both AMD FreeSync Premium Pro and Nvidia G-Sync Compatible technologies while the Sony only supports AMD FreeSync Premium Pro.   																   \n\nStand Positions - The Sony A95L comes packaged with a video camera that allows you to adjust stand positions more easily than with other models such as the Samsung S95B, which does not come with this feature included.    \n\nSamsung S95C vs Sony A90J: 5 Must-Know Facts    &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  &nbsp;&nbsp;\n&nbsp;&nbsp;1) The Samsung S95B was released in 2021 while the Sony A90K was released in 2022; however both are considered top of line models for their respective brands as they both make use of advanced display technologies like Quantum Dot (QD) OLED for better picture quality and brightness levels compared to traditional LEDs or LCDs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;\n&nbsp;&nbsp;2) While both models offer excellent picture quality, there are some differences between them when it comes to color accuracy; specifically, the Samsung model offers more accurate colors due to its use of QD technology whereas traditional OLEDs tend to suffer from slight inaccuracies in color reproduction when compared side by side with QD models like this one from Samsung\n\n', 1, '2023-03-03', '13:31:58', '2023-03-03 10:29:20');
