(649, 'H+92xWi3GyAlDUzP8F55zA==', 161, '<p>Are you looking to dive into the world of programming, but feeling overwhelmed by the sheer number of programming languages to choose from? If so, you\'re not alone. Choosing the right programming language can be a daunting task, especially if you\'re new to the field. In this article, we\'ll be taking a closer look at two of the most popular scripting languages out there: Ruby and JavaScript.</p><p>Ruby vs JavaScript: Side-by-Side Comparison</p><p>Before we dive into the differences between Ruby and JavaScript, let\'s take a look at a side-by-side comparison of these two languages:</p><ul><li>Ruby is an object-oriented programming language, while JavaScript is a scripting language.</li><li>Ruby was developed by Yukihiro \"Matz\" Matsumoto in the mid-1990s, while JavaScript was developed by Brendan Eich in 1995.</li><li>Ruby is often used for web development, as well as for creating scripts and automation tools. JavaScript, on the other hand, is primarily used for web development and is a key component of web browsers.</li><li>Ruby has a more concise and expressive syntax compared to JavaScript, which can sometimes be verbose and repetitive.</li><li>Ruby has a strong focus on simplicity and readability, whereas JavaScript\'s design philosophy emphasizes flexibility and adaptability.</li><li>Ruby uses a unique programming paradigm called \"duck typing,\" while JavaScript uses prototype-based programming.</li><li>Ruby code is typically easier to read and understand, while JavaScript code can sometimes be difficult to decipher due to its dynamic nature.</li></ul>', 1, '2023-03-23', '16:00:22', '2023-03-23 12:56:20'),
