br></p><p>Symbols have their place in the modern world,</p><p>But the interpretation must be able to be unfurled,</p><p>It\'s no longer acceptable to take them at face value,</p><p>We must be critical and question, that\'s the rational we must solve.</p><p><br></p><p>As for naivety, it takes a special kind of irrational boldness,</p><p>To cling to superstition and ignore scientific evidence,</p><p>Without questioning the validity of its source,</p><p>And calling it a day without any recourse.</p><p><br></p><p>You\'re something of a clod,</p><p>If you don\'t have the courage to be critical of what these old disciplines teach,</p><p>Do not be ashamed of your naivety,</p><p>But instead strive for veritable knowledge that\'s rooted in logic!</p><p>So, when it comes to ancient ways of thinking,</p><p>Don\'t be afraid to challenge assumptions,</p><p>And embrace empirical evidence for solutions.</p><p><br></p><p>Otherwise, if dedicating time to studying symbols is what you choose,</p><p>I\'d suggest you arm yourself with knowledge and facts,</p><p>And be open to critical examination and scientific inquiry.</p><p>So don\'t be afraid to ask questions,</p><p>And use science to prove the assertions,</p><p>For the future is here, and it\'s time to move on.</p><p><br></p><p>Your a priori argument is a fallacy, if not a fallacy of logic,</p><p>So it\'s time to break away from symbols and mythic,</p><p>And embrace the modern world with its science and logic,</p><p>And leave the old ways behind, where they belong,</p><p>In the realm of myth and superstition,</p><p>Now, where do I claim compensation for bearing your incoherent retort?</p></div><div class=\"ql-clipboard\" tabindex=\"-1\" contenteditable=\"true\"></div><div class=\"ql-tooltip ql-hidden\"><a class=\"ql-preview\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"blank\" rel=\"noopener\"></a><input type=\"text\" data-formula=\"e=mc^2\" data-link=\"https://quilljs.com\" data-video=\"Embed URL\"><a class=\"ql-action\"></a><a class=\"ql-remove\"></