the other advising throwing caution to the wind, countless series bear the same blueprint of a holy vs a rubble rousing friend and this is by design.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAs far as naivety goes, it takes a special sort of stupid for a man to discard knowledge in the name of being archaic and outdated, while better men than you have sought to consolidate the importance of symbolism in this modern world.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nI gave an example of the Qatari world cup insignia bearing the resemblance of Ourubus, a snake devouring it\'s own tail.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAnother I\'ll provide is primitive tribes preference to exemplify a virtue by an animal, Kings in Africa preferring lions and leopard skins, Kings in Europe preference for Wolf and bear fur, stone age paintings of animals found deep in caves, Ancient Egyptians with Seth..and tons more.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nUnlike you I don\'t pout my bony chest out and proclaim that certain works of esteemed mind are nonsense nor hoist my skirts up and turn my nose on knowledge because it predates the first time I burst a nut.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nI intend to dedicate a huge chunk of 2023 to study subjective symbols, and if that earns me shame of naivety then so be it, society as is stands currently is full of sh\'t anyway.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nMike:\r\n\r\nWhen you put words in my mouth like that,\r\n\r\nit takes to reason that you be taken to task,\r\n\r\nFor I never said that Jung\'s works were nonsense,\r\n\r\nonly that they should be subjected to rigors of modern science.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nYour type have the tendency to see shadows in the dark,\r\n\r\nwhen the light of logic and reason can illuminate your heart,\r\n\r\nYour case in point of the Qatar insignia,\r\n\r\nis no proof that superstition should not be questioned,\r\n\r\nAs for stone age paintings and ancient Egyptians,\r\n\r\nThey are part of history,\r\n\r\nnot the present day equation.\r\n\r\nCause and coincidence are not to be confounded,\r\n\r\nAnd I\'m afraid your approach precludes further discourse along that course.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe interpretation of symbols depends on the individual,\r\n\r\nWhich is why it\'s imperative to be critical and question them in a scientific way,\r\n\r\nSo that the truth is revealed and not what we want to hear.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSymbols have their place in the modern world,\r\n\r\nBut the interpretation must be able to be unfurled,\r\n\r\nIt\'s no longer acceptable to take them at face value,\r\n\r\nWe must be critical and question, that\'s the rational we must solve.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAs for naivety, it takes a special kind of irrational boldness,\r\n\r\nTo cling to superstition and ignore scientific evidence,\r\n\r\nWithout questioning the validity of its source,\r\n\r\nAnd calling it a day without any recourse.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nYou\'re something of a clod,\r\n\r\nIf you don\'t have the courage to be critical of what these old disciplines teach,\r\n\r\nDo not be ashamed of your naivety,\r\n\r\nBut instead strive for veritable knowledge that\'s rooted in logic!\r\n\r\nSo, when it comes to ancient ways of thinking,\r\n\r\nDon\'t be afraid to challenge assumptions,\r\n\r\nAnd embrace empirical evidence for solutions.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nOtherwise, if dedicating time to studying symbols is what you choose,\r\n\r\nI\'d suggest you arm yourself with knowledge and facts,\r\n\r\nAnd be open to critical examination and scientific inquiry.\r\n\r\nSo don\'t be afraid to ask questions,\r\n\r\nAnd use science to prove the assertions,\r\n\r\nFor the future is here, and it\'s time to move on.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nYour a priori argument is a fallacy, if not a fallacy of logic,\r\n\r\nSo it\'s time to break away from symbols and mythic,\r\n\r\nAnd embrace the modern world with its science and logic,\r\n\r\nAnd leave the old ways behind, where they belong,\r\n\r\nIn the realm of myth and superstition,\r\n\r\nNow, where do I claim compensation for bearing your incoherent retort?\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"ql-clipboard\" tabindex=\"-1\" contenteditable=\"true\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"ql-tooltip ql-hidden\"><input type=\"text\" data-formula=\"e=mc^2\" data-link=\"https://quilljs.com\" data-video=\"Embed URL\" /></div>', 'Symbology, numerology, astrology, metaphysics', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '48-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-01-04 09:18:46', '2023-01-04 09:18:46', '', 48, 'http://localhost/parrot/blog/?p=50', 0, 'revision', '', 0);

